article.description: Amauri Hardy fueled a game-ending 27-7 run with nine of his 20 points and UNLV pulled away from Jackson State 80-57 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Hardy leads the way as UNLV tops Jackson State 80-57
article.linkText: Hardy leads the way as UNLV tops Jackson State 80-57
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Amauri Hardy fueled a game-ending 27-7 run with nine of his 20 points and UNLV pulled away from Jackson State 80-57 on Tuesday night. Cheikh Mbacke Diong added 19 points and 13 rebounds as the Runnin' Rebels turned a three-point game into a route. Bryce Hamilton had 12 points and Nick Blair 10 for UNLV (3-5). UNLV went 10 of 15 with a pair of 3-pointers down the stretch while Tigers were just 3 of 11 with six turnovers. Tristan Jarrett scored 23 points for the Tigers (1-6). --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25
